	(text "Decoupling:\n\n10 uF  : low-frequency, high draw (wifi)\n0.1 uF : high-frequency\n1 uF   : mid-band\n\nThis is in line with the decoupling approach/guidelines used in the CAD assignment.\n\nIt is also consistent with the ESP32-S3 Hardware Design Guidelines:\n\n\"For VDD3P3, when ESP32-S3 is transmitting signals, there may be a sudden increase in the current draw, causing\npower rail collapse. Therefore, it is highly recommended to add a 10 μF capacitor to the power rail, which can work\nin conjunction with the 1 μF capacitor(s) or other capacitors.\""
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 18.542 68.58 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.762 0.762)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "426dac83-9331-4345-9a8c-37f2b9377b53")
	)
